					<head>Jewish law</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Fragments of the Babylonian Talmud.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="tmr" otherLangs="he">Aramaic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="102v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Talmud bavli</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תלמוד בבלי</title>
							<note>
								<p>The Mishnah of each chapter is given in its entirety  before Gemara begins, as in Harley MS 5508 and Or 5530.</p>
								<p>The manuscript is, unlike Harley MS 5508, exceedingly well written. The marginal notes, in a later cursive hand, represent an attempt at comparing the printed edition with the manuscript.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. Harley MS 5508, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">400</ref> and Or 5530, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">399</ref>.</filiation>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="44r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Berakhot</title>
								<note>
									<p>The greater portion of the first chapter is missing. </p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="44v" to="72v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">‘Arakhin  </title>
								<note>
									<p>The two missing leaves after folio 66 contained a small portion of the 7th chapter and a larger portion of the 8th.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="72v" to="102v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Keritot</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the end of the 13th or beginning of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>102 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>255</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>235</height>
										<width>185</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>102 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Folios 1-101: 13 quires of originally 8 leaves each. One leaf is missing after folio 52, and two leaves are wanting after folio 66.</p>
									<p>Folio 102 begins a new quire, the subsequent leaves of which are currently missing. </p>
									<p>About 1 quire is missing at the beginning.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Defective at the beginning and at the end.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Each page on folios 1-80 is divided into 2 columns of 30 lines each; on folio 89-102 the page consists of a single column of 30 lines.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point regular ruling.</p>
									<p>Flesh side and hair side distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Many marginal notes supplied by a later cursive hand.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Ashkenazi (Greek style) square script of the end of the 13th or beginning of the 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Blind-tooled brown leather. Modern BL box.</p>
								<p>Spine title: Tractatus Talmudici. Tres. Hebr. Mus. Brit. Iure Empt. 25, 717.'</p>
							</binding>
